####################################
# Compiling the kernel assignments #
####################################

# Configure os161
cd ~/os161/
./configure --ostree="$HOME/os161/root" --toolprefix="sos-"

# Configure kernel assignment
cd kern/conf
./config ASST0

cd ../compile/ASST0

# Make kernel assignment
# Be sure to use "bmake" regular make will fail. 
bmake depend
bmake
bmake install

# Make os161
cd ~/os161
bmake

# Copy the sys161 conf (probably only need to do this once)
cp ~/sys161/sys161.conf root

# Run assignment
cd root
sys161 kernel-ASST0

##################
# Toolchain Info #
##################

All toolchain binaries for os-161 (gcc, gdb, etc.) start with sos-

Here is a list: 

sos-addr2line
sos-ar
sos-as
sos-c++filt
sos-cpp
sos-gcc
sos-gcc-4.1.2
sos-gccbug
sos-gcov
sos-gdb
sos-gdbtui
sos-ld
sos-nm
sos-objcopy
sos-objdump
sos-ranlib
sos-readelf
sos-run
sos-size
sos-strings
sos-strip

they live in ~/sys161/bin (which is a symlink)

